 be\nborne on the laser stability requirement in view of recent progress in laser\nstability. Compared with X, Y and Z, the X+Y+Z configuration does have a good\ncancellation of path length differences and could serve as a null string\ndetection check. We compile and compare the resulting differences of various\nTDI configurations due to the different arm lengths for various LISA-like\nmission proposals and for the ASTROD-GW mission proposal.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Jul 2017 07:16:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 10 Dec 2017 02:07:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-26"}
