. The relationships\nbetween the size (S), lifetime (T), and the flux (F) for patches in the QS,\nindicate the power$-$law relationships $S\\propto T~^{0.25}$ and $F\\propto\nT~^{0.38}$, respectively. Executing a detrended fluctuation analysis of the\ntime series of new emerged magnetic elements, we find a Hurst exponent of 0.82,\nwhich implies long-range temporal correlation in the system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Jul 2017 15:50:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-31"}
